HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1644
By Salinas
A RESOLUTION to honor the residents of Frayser on the
celebration of their neighborhood's 200th
anniversary.
WHEREAS, it is fitting that we should join with the communities that comprise this great
State in celebrating joyous and notable occasions in their histories; and
WHEREAS, Frayser, a neighborhood on the north side of Memphis, is celebrating its
200th anniversary this year; and
WHEREAS, named after Memphis physician Dr. J. Frayser, Frayser is home to
approximately 45,000 citizens, who live within the neighborhood's boundaries of the Wolf River
to the south, the Mississippi River to the west, the Loosahatchie River to the north, and the
Illinois Central Railroad tracks to the east; and
WHEREAS, the area now known as Frayser was settled in the 1820s, when Italian
settlers purchased farmland in the area; the community was annexed by the City of Memphis in
1958; and
WHEREAS, Frayser is home to the Memphis Business Academy middle school and high
school, the Ed Rice Community Center, and many public parks, including North Frayser
Community Center and Pickett Park, Shivler Park, Firestone Park, and Davy Crockett Park; and
WHEREAS, for 200 years, the good people of Frayser have added immeasurably to the
strength and character of the State of Tennessee; their history and accomplishments have
contributed significantly to the cultural richness for which this State is known; and
WHEREAS, it is most appropriate that we should honor this fine community and its
residents as they commemorate this significant milestone in their shared existence; now,
therefore,
HJR1644
018559
- 1 -

BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and congratulate the residents of Frayser on the celebration of
their neighborhood's 200th anniversary and extend to them our best wishes for continued
success, growth, and prosperity in their vibrant, historic community.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
